<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900919-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>900919-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Lomas Financial Corp.:   Net Loss of $44.1 Million   Posted for Fiscal 4th Period</HL><DATE>09/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10</SO><CO>   LFC</CO><IN>DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES, FANNIE MAE, FREDDIE MAC (FIS)EARNINGS (ERN)BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)</IN><LP>   Lomas Financial Corp. reported profit from continuingoperations of $4.9 million, or seven cents a share, for thefourth quarter ended June 30, compared with a loss fromcontinuing operations of $282.9 million, or $7.69 a share, inthe year-earlier period.   The Dallas financial-services and real-estate concern saidlosses from discontinued operations of $49 million led to anet loss of $44.1 million, or $1.25 a share, on revenue of$69.9 million. In the year-earlier period, losses fromdiscontinued operations of $20.3 million resulted in a netloss of $303 million, or $8.26 a share, on revenue of $77.2million.</LP><TEXT>   Lomas has been operating under protection from creditorsunder Chapter 11 of the U.S. Bankruptcy Code since last Sept.24.   For the year, Lomas reported a net loss of $695.5 million,or $19.07 a share, including losses from discontinuedoperations of $243 million and losses from continuingoperations of $452.4 million, on revenue of $290 million.   In the year-earlier period, the company reported a netloss of $298.2 million, or $8.24 a share, including lossesfrom continuing operations of $311.7 million, a loss fromdiscontinued operations of $2.2 million and an extraordinarygain from retirement of debt of $15.7 million, on revenue of$334 million.</TEXT></DOC>